Before running:
------------------------
1) Copy test.csh, run_all_tests.csh to your project directory.
2) Make sure the test.csh, run_all_tests.csh have the execute permission.
   Otherwise, use
   $$$]% chmod +x ./test.csh
   $$$]% chmod +x ./run_all_tests.csh

Usage:
------
$$$]% ./run_all_tests.csh 
        --> to run all the tests and generate the "grade.txt"
$$$]% ./test.csh <test_nr> 
        --> to run a particular test 



Following are 21 released test cases: (test1.c to test21.c)

// PASS
0     : existence of "makefile" and "readme"
1     : if "make" create "libmem.so" in current directory
2     : whether your proram uses "malloc()", you should not use global array either
3     : Mem_Init - sizeOfRegion is zero
4     : Mem_Init - two consecutive calls
5     : Mem_Alloc - not enough free memory
6     : Mem_Alloc - zero size

//FAIL
7    : Mem_Free - null pointer
8    : Mem_Alloc and Mem_Free - series of calls
9    : Debug - stale padding
10    : Debug - stale free space
11    : Debug - not enough memory (but it works in non-debug mode)
12    : Debug - simple merging of free memory chunks
13    : Performance test - see ./out for your time, your prog should not crash
14    : Debug - correct padding with 
15    : Debug - correct free space pattern 
16    : Debug - simple successful call 
17    : Debug - Mem_Free with pointer out of scope 
18    : more complicated merging 
19    : Rigorous stress test with rounds of alloc and free 
20    : Debug - stale padding again 
